x4freetext: Supplement Number 2.

.Powder for transmission.
.Thin metal plate for scattering.
.Transmission in the energy range of 627 to 4216 eV
was done at 77 deg-K, others were at 293 deg-K.
Time of flight, flight path = 53.7 and
103.7 m for transmission, and 32.7 m for scattering.
Boron 1 to 2 cm thick and 6 Na-I crystals
(dia 125 mm, height 50 mm) for transmission.
- Boron loaded liquid scintillator for
scattering.
Shape analysis on normalized transmission
data. For details see CEA-N-1149.
.The resonance at 1.257 eV was not analyzed by author
but used for the averaged resonance parameters.
The following values were taken (see REL-REF):
Resonance parameters +- error in per-cent,
gamma     2g*gamma(n)  gamma(gamma)  spin  momentum l
.One resonance energy and 3 gamma(tot) error values
were misprinted. (Oral priv.comm. from Ribon).
approved by Ribon.
